# SYNAPSE Guardrails Domain
# Behavioral rules for the Guardrails Tips System

# When tips are shown, follow these rules:
# 1. Present tips as suggestions, never block execution
# 2. If user ignores a tip, do not repeat it for the same prompt
# 3. Handoff suggestions include the exact command to execute
# 4. Tips are capped at ~300 tokens to minimize context usage
# 5. Use *tips off to disable, *tips on to re-enable, *tips stats for metrics

GUARDRAILS_RULES:
  - Tips are advisory only — never block user actions
  - Show max 1 tip per prompt (highest confidence)
  - Skip tips for star-commands, confirmations, and short prompts
  - Include trigger command in handoff suggestions when available
  - Track history for learning boosts (max 500 entries)
